---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout title="About" description="About b4rt and dumpthecore — a developer blog about Linux, systems, cloud, and debugging.">
  <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.03em; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 2rem;">
    About
  </h1>

  <div class="prose prose-neutral max-w-none">
    <h2>About me</h2>
    <p>
      Hi, I'm <strong>b4rt</strong>. I work with software, Linux, cloud, systems, and infrastructure. Basically, I spend my time solving real problems and, from time to time, creating entirely new ones.
    </p>
    <p>
      Dump The Core exists because I like understanding how things work underneath: services, networks, containers, systems, automation, security, hardware, IoT, and anything else that seems like a good idea at 2am.
    </p>

    <h2>What I write about</h2>
    <p>
      Posts about Linux, cloud, debugging, backend, security, automation, IoT, electronics, and failures with a lot of educational value once they're over.
    </p>

    <h2>The setup</h2>
    <p>
      Astro, MDX, git, and Cloudflare. No CMS. No database. No extra fluff. Just text, ideas, and the occasional bad decision pushed to production.
    </p>
    <p>
      Yes, there's also a light theme. It exists for legal reasons.<br />
      And yes, I use Arch, btw.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      I can't promise a fast reply, but I can promise that if something breaks, there's a good chance I'll end up writing about it.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="mailto:b4rt@linux.com">b4rt@linux.com</a>
    </p>

    <h2>RSS</h2>
    <p>
      Yes, there's <a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a>. As it should be.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
